  "Allegations" : "Respondent Towers failed to respond to FINRA request for information. On September 17, 2015, pursuant to FINRA Rule 9552, FINRA issued a Notice of Suspension to Respondent for his failure to provide information, which was requested in accordance with FINRA Rule 8210. The Notice informed Respondent that: (i) he would be suspended effective October 13, 2015, if he did not take corrective action by that date; (ii) he could request a hearing by October 13, 2015, pursuant to Rule 9552(e), which would stay the effective date of the suspension; and (iii) he would be automatically barred, pursuant to Rule 9552(h), effective December 21, 2015, if he did not request termination of his suspension.",
