  "Regulator Statement" : "On October 7, 2015, Respondent timely filed a request for a hearing pursuant to FINRA Rule 9552(e), staying the imposition of the suspension. A hearing is scheduled in this matter for December 2-3, 2015. On November 27, 2015, Respondent filed a Notice withdrawing his request for a hearing. Accordingly, Respondent's request for a hearing was dismissed, and FINRA's September 17, 2015, Notice of Suspension constitutes FINRA's final action in this proceeding. As set forth in the Notice of Suspension, and with the issuance of the Order, Respondent was immediately suspended from associating with any member firm in any capacity, pursuant to Rule 9552(e), and he is therefore barred from associating with any member firm in any capacity, effective December 21, 2015, pursuant to Rule 9552(h).   Thus; pursuant to FINRA Rule 9552(h) and in accordance with FINRA's Notice of Suspension and Suspension from Association letters dated September 17, 2015 and October 13, 2015, respectively, on December 21, 2015, Towers is barred from association with any FINRA member in any capacity. Respondent failed to request termination of his suspension within three months of the date of the Notice of Suspension; therefore, he is automatically barred from association with any FINRA member in any capacity.  Associated case number is Expedited Proceeding No. FPI150010"
}

